# ===================================
# 🚀 AUTHENTICATION BYPASS CONFIGURATION
# ===================================
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: For production use, always use your own Stripe keys
# The keys above are for testing purposes only

# 📋 Authentication Setup:
# 1. Users can access their accounts without logging into Stripe
# 2. Platform authentication handles access control
# 3. Stripe Connect embedded components bypass login requirements
# 4. Each user gets their own Stripe Connect Express account automatically

# 🔐 How it works:
# - Users sign in with email/password (no Stripe login required)
# - Platform creates/retrieves their Stripe Connect account
# - All embedded components use disable_stripe_user_authentication: true
# - Users manage payments, payouts, account settings through your platform
# - No direct Stripe dashboard access needed

# 🏗️ Account Types Supported:
# - Express Accounts (created automatically on signup)
# - Custom Accounts (for advanced use cases)
# - Demo Accounts (for testing)

# 💡 Benefits:
# ✅ Seamless user experience - no Stripe login required
# ✅ Brand consistency - everything in your platform
# ✅ Simplified onboarding - automatic account creation
# ✅ Full control - you manage the user experience
# ✅ Secure - uses platform Stripe secret key for authentication

# 🛠️ To deploy to production:
# 1. Replace the keys above with your own Stripe keys
# 2. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL to your production domain
# 3. Set STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET to your production webhook secret
# 4. Configure any additional security measures needed